---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Work" description="What I have been doing lately - Felipe Lamarca">
  <div class="space-y-12">
    <header>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">My Work</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">What I have been doing lately</p>
    </header>

    <section class="space-y-8">
      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
          Data Scientist <span class="text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500">@</span> <a href="https://atlasintel.org/" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">AtlasIntel</a>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          AtlasIntel provides advanced data products for political intelligence and economic forecasting. I'm currently working on calibrating survey samples, political analysis, public opinion monitoring, and improving internal data pipelines.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Researcher <span class="text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500">@</span> IESP-UERJ</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
              <a href="https://mape.org.br/" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MAPE</a>
              <span class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 font-normal text-sm ml-1">· coordinated by Fernando Meireles &amp; Bruno Schaefer</span>
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1 leading-relaxed">Policy and Election Monitoring and Evaluation Laboratory. Dedicated to studying public policy, elections, and their interconnections using causal inference and machine learning techniques.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
              <a href="https://www.lab-doxa.org.br/" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">DOXA</a>
              <span class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 font-normal text-sm ml-1">· coordinated by Fernando Meireles &amp; Argelina Cheibub Figueiredo</span>
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1 leading-relaxed">Laboratory of Electoral Studies, Political Communication and Public Opinion. A leading center for research on electoral processes, political communication, and voting behavior in Brazil.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
              <a href="http://necon.iesp.uerj.br" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NECON</a>
              <span class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 font-normal text-sm ml-1">· coordinated by Fabiano Santos</span>
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1 leading-relaxed">Center for Studies on Congress. Focused on academic research on the Brazilian legislature, including databases on nominal votes, party migration, and legislative production.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
        Before joining AtlasIntel, MAPE, DOXA, and NECON, I provided data science and research consulting services to both industry (Roberto Marinho Foundation, Artplan, Visagio) and academia (FGV EBAPE, CEBRAP, GENI/UFF). Please check my <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1dFBrI109flg6zSQHnFIxUd1DRfieCYAT/view" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CV</a> for more information on my work experience.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="section-title">Awards & Distinctions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
